VThePallavishe coined forMohana Krishna Shyama Brindavana Sarangahad names of the mainragasand was done in Chaturasra Triputataalam. It was a great exercise that received thunderous applause. The number reflected the vocalist&#8217;s urge to be different and creative, but never losing the sight of melodic element and adhering to all the principles of Carnatic music. There was also another majorragaeffort of Kharaharapriya for the popular Thyagaraja numberPrakkala Nilabadiwithnerevalandswaras.Mngambudhi Hanumantha,a composition of Annamacharya also figured here. She had a strong team of accompanists in Sanjeev&#8217;s violin and Satish Kumar&#8217;s mridangam. P.V.Ramanamurthy gave another percussion support on ghatam.The expression ofsahityawas of poor quality. For those who wished to enjoy thekirtanaand its melody, even thenerevalandswarakalpanatoo were a bit disappointing. He chose Bhagesri for hisRagam-Tanam-Pallavieffort which had a limited scope to match the depths of Pallavi.  Yet he succeeded to present it well.Thetani avartanamby the percussion duo was another highlight.
